  "slug": "who-told-me-investing-wasnt-for-women-like-me",
  "title": "Who Told Me Investing Wasn't for Women Like Me?",
  "subtitle": "A journal prompt set for tracing the roots of the exclusion belief around investing",
  "excerpt": "A journal set for locating the source of the investing-isn't-for-me belief. Works through who taught it, what the household relationship with investment was, and what would need to be true for investing to feel accessible.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A journal set for tracing the investing-isn't-for-me belief back to its source. Most exclusion beliefs about money were absorbed from households where certain kinds of money behaviour were normal and others were not modelled at all.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journal practice? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is my current relationship with investing?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you have a pension? A stocks-and-shares ISA? Anything? Or has investing been something you've thought about and not started?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does the word 'investor' bring up for me?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who do you picture? Does that person look like you?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Did anyone in my household invest when I was growing up?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If yes, what did you hear about it? If not, what did that absence communicate?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who specifically told me (or showed me) that this wasn't for people like me?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It might not have been words. It might have been the absence of a conversation, the people in the adverts, the assumption that financial decisions were handled by someone else.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What would need to be true for me to consider myself someone who invests?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write the full list without editing. Then look at each condition and mark the ones that are beliefs, not facts.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
